main event: A report concerning an unidentified flying object sighted over Baltimore, Maryland on November 6, 1957.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to the Air Force but was not evaluated due to lack of evidence,The object was described as unusual and sparked a follow-up inquiry from the observer,The observer had experience as an amateur astronomer and stated they had never seen anything like it before,No other sightings were recorded in the Baltimore area on the incident date according to Air Force files,Several letters were exchanged between the observer and the Air Force seeking information about the sighting.
witness description: An amateur astronomer who viewed the object on November 6, 1957.
